events.description: Weekly report on US crude oil inventory levels for the week ended January 30th, 2025.

facts.fact_text: US crude oil inventories decreased by 11.1 million barrels in the week ended January 30th, 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: US crude oil inventories plunged by 11.1 million barrels in the week ended January 30th, 2025

facts.fact_text: The inventory draw significantly exceeded market expectations of a 0.7 million barrel build.

evidences.evidence_text: The decrease sharply contrasted with expectations for a 0.7 million barrel build

facts.fact_text: The 11.1 million barrel drop is the largest decline in inventories since August 2023.

evidences.evidence_text: to mark the sharpest decline since August 2023

facts.fact_text: Crude oil inventories had a 0.25 million-barrel draw in the week prior to January 30th.

evidences.evidence_text: extending a 0.25 million-barrel draw in the prior week
